caption: I placed an order through their online ordering service just to arrive to the restaurant just to see that they are closed until Friday... Now I have an almost $40 dollar meal tied up.....  UPDATE: The restaurant is still closed and I’ve contacted support as requested and I was advised the order is still waiting to be accepted or declined by the store and that they can tissue a refund, I’m at the store right now and it is still closed, When will the store reopen so that I can either get my food i’ve been waiting for or a refund, please let me know

The food is good. Now let's talk service. The service I've received has been exceedingly poor. I've ordered there for my coworkers a few times. This is the third time that they have either 'run out of food' or 'closed' after my order has been placed and the money received. I've called and I spoke to someone once...who relayed that they had run out of food, at 8am in the morning. Okay.... other times they just let the phone ring. Today's order was my last from this company. Once placed, the order was accepted and I received the "they're working on it" notification.  Then they sent me an "update order" option because they didn't have any of those food items. As I'm updating, the store closes. So now my coworkers and I have to wait for the money to be restored to my account. This 'restaurant ' is ridiculous.  What restaurant,  dinner, or food stall runs out of food first thing in the morning? Order at your own risk.... it'll be kicked back more times then not.

They came to my work today through the food program.  So so so so so so many much better Asian style restaurants to eat at in Atlanta. They had rice that looked like it was overcooked, filled with cheap green beans and corn bits that look like it came out of a 75 cent can. (if you are going to run an Asian style resutrant you have to get the rice correct).  The quality of the meat was gross. I got the pork, very bland, super chewy with lots of tendons.  The sides they had to go along with rice / noddle bowls were Asian slaw (that was okay) and things like black beans, shredded cheese, and pico de gallo (the tomatoes looked like they were poor quality and super watery, could see through the slices they were so transparent). How on earth do beans and shredded cheese go along with Korean glass noodles?  My expectations for lunch catering is never very high, but this was by far the worst restaurant to ever come through the Foda program.

What a cool place.  At its most basic level, it's a Korean Moe's in that you pick what you'd like to have on your burrito/bowl, and they make it in front of you.  But the ingredients you can choose from is where things get interesting, and its what makes this place unique and awesome.  You have a variety of korean/southern fusion proteins and toppings to choose from, such as beef bulgogi, pickled daikon, and KIMCHI PIMIENTO CHEESE (yes!).  Everything I tried was delicious.  Though the burrito/bowl bar seems to be the obvious choice, they also offer a variety of other entrees that are cooked fresh to order, such as a bulgogi philly, korean fried chicken, and quesadillas.  I had the fried chicken sandwich (which comes with fried pickles on it), with added daikon and kimchi pimiento and it was fantastic.  The sesame fries are also sweet deliciousness.  I highly recommend this place for something different!  Also, the customer service is stellar.  The employees are more than willing to tell you about any ingredient that might pique your interest,  and they are just friendly in general.  Thanks!

I ordered the burrito with teriyaki chicken, kimchi pimento, guac, and other delicious toppings. It was AMAZING! Very delicious! The customer service was great. Everything was made fresh. I will be back soon!

First 2 times I visited, I had the Korean fried chicken sandwich.  Was really good.  It was freshly cooked, so you have to wait a bit. But was worth it.  My third time was a disaster.   Ketchup for my fries was a dirty Heinz bottle like the ones you would by at the grocery store.  And my sandwich was tough, like it's warmed over.  They need to do a better job training their service staff.  Not professional at all.

I tried a breakfast sandwich a coworker ordered just a couple weeks ago and it was so delicious! The sandwich had many layers of flavors. I went to SoKoMe today, and the recipe had completely changed. A sandwich that once had kimchi pimento cheese, a delicious sauce, and other toppings is now just a bun with sausage and cheese. For the same price. The sandwich had zero Southern, Korean or Mexican elements, which I understood to be the cornerstone of their brand. The sandwich was good, and would have be given a higher rating, but the disappointment in the menu change is to blame for the low rating.
